example.p:
The explicit formula for the sequence uses the function \displaystyle f(n)=\frac{n}{2n+1} for integer values of n. We can think of the continuous function n \overset{f}\mapsto x defined for arbitrary values of n The inverse f^{-1}: x \mapsto n can inform us of when the sequence reaches different values.
x = \frac{n}{2n+1} (2n+1)x = n 2n x + x = n 2n x - n = -x (2x-1) n = -x n = \frac{-x}{2x-1} = \frac{x}{1-2x}
This function, \displaystyle f^{-1}(x)=\frac{x}{1-2x}, gives the relation x \mapsto n.

li.p:
The problem can be solved up if we just factor out from the numerator and denominator 
the dominant term (greatest power) and simplify as needed. 

  \lim_{n \to \infty} \frac{n^2-3n}{5n-1} & = \lim_{n \to \infty} \frac{n^2(1-\frac{3}{n})}{n(5-\frac{1}{n})} 
   & = \lim_{n \to \infty} \frac{n(1-\frac{3}{n})}{5-\frac{1}{n}} 
   & = \frac{+\infty \cdot(1-\frac{3}{\infty})}{5-\frac{1}{\infty}}
   & = \frac{+\infty\cdot 1}{5} = +\infty.

solution.p:
Solve the fixed point equation, f(x)=x:
2.7x-0.7x^2 = x 1.7x - 0.7x^2 = 0 x(1.7-0.7x) = 0 x=0 \quad \hbox{or} \quad 1.7-0.7x = 0 x=0 \quad \hbox{or} \quad x = \frac{17}{7}
There are two fixed points, x=0 and x=\frac{17}{7}. The decimal approximation for \frac{17}{7} is 2.42857, and we have found the limit, \lim_{n \to \infty} z_n = \frac{17}{7}.
